HEADWORD: Outbrag
<hw>Out*brag"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To surpass in
bragging; hence, to make appear inferior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whose bare <qex>outbragg'd</qex> the web it seemed to wear.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outbrave</ent>⟦br⟧
